After installed Team Calendars 4.1.4, when trying to print in Google Chrome (test in Firefox, but, wasn't able to find the Preview window for printing), the page tittle is not displayed properly. 

h4.Steps to Reproduce

# Install Team Calendars 4.1.4 version
# Try to print any page and check for the preview.
# The expected behaviour is: 
!tcp.png!

After installing Team Calendars, the page tittle doesn't display properly: 
!tcpe.png!

This issue could be related to other printing issues found in [TEAMCAL-2032|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/TEAMCAL-2032].

Information tracked from the reporter, which should be the workaround for this issue: 

{quote}

The css generated when printing any page in my production instance produces:
{code}
/* module-key = 'com.atlassian.confluence.extra.team-calendars:calendar-resources', location = 'com/atlassian/confluence/extra/calendar3/css/printing.css' */
...
#main-header{display:none;}
...
{code}

If I change this to:

{code}
#main-header{display:inline;}
{code}

The header is re-displayed. The page metadata continues to display (as it sort of did before) but it slightly overlaps the header because the margin is set to -15px. Thus, if I apply the following customized stylesheet to my space, the issue is entirely resolved:

{code}
@media print{  
     .page-metadata{  
         margin:0px 0 20px !important;  
     }  
     #main-header{  
       display: inline !important;  
     }  
}  
{code}
{quote}

